(166, 2, '2012-09-05 02:21:38', '2012-09-05 02:21:38', 'I need a job, where do I look?\nWhat job should I be looking for?\nShould I flood the job market with my resume?\nAll questions that run through our minds when we are looking for a job.\nNo don’t “flood the job market with your resume”, you aren’t showing you are in demand, rather you look desperate.\nNetworking is a key ingredient to a successful search, so start by looking at http://www.linkedin.com\nWhat type of job or career do you really want? This is the crux of the job search today. Identify what you really like doing and get paid.\nDon’t just look for a job rather look for a person or company that will help lead you to the job.\n', 'Job Search', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '34-autosave', '', '', '2012-09-05 02:21:38', '2012-09-05 02:21:38', '', 34, 'http://wecareerresources.com/%page-name%/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
